{"sections":{"main":{"type":"main-page","disabled":true,"settings":{"subheading":"","show_title":true,"heading_font_size":"heading-large","show_content":true,"text_font_size":"body-medium","align_text":"text-left","width":"wrapper","color_scheme":"","padding_top":50,"padding_bottom":50,"heading_tag":"automatic"}},"double-1":{"type":"section-double","blocks":{"heading-1-1":{"type":"heading","settings":{"title":"Moissanite - The Gem from the Stars","heading_font_size":"heading-large","padding_bottom":16,"heading_tag":"automatic"}},"text-1-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>Moissanite, known as “the gem from the stars,” was first discovered in 1893 by French chemist Henri Moissan at a meteorite site in Arizona. Initially mistaken for diamonds, it wasn’t until 1904 that Moissan identified it as a completely new mineral, later named Moissanite in his honor.<br\/><br\/>Natural Moissanite is extremely rare, usually found near meteorite impact sites or occasionally with rough diamonds. Its scarcity and unpredictable formation under extreme conditions make it far more than just a diamond alternative—it is a unique rarity of its own.<\/p>","text_font_size":"body-medium","padding_bottom":16}}},"block_order":["heading-1-1","text-1-1"],"settings":{"image_1":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Moissanite_-_The_Gem_from_the_Stars.jpg","image_width":"one-half","text_alignment":"text-left","layout":"is-reversed","width":"wrapper--full","height":"image-height","mobile_height":"image-height--mobile","reverse_blocks":false,"color_scheme":"","padding_top":0,"padding_bottom":50,"show_placeholder":true}},"double-2":{"type":"section-double","blocks":{"heading-2-1":{"type":"heading","settings":{"title":"","heading_font_size":"heading-large","padding_bottom":16,"heading_tag":"automatic"}},"text-2-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>To meet the growing demand for this exceptional stone, scientists have successfully replicated the unique characteristics of natural Moissanite in laboratory-grown variants. Through continuous refinement and enhancements, driven by scientific advancements and valuable customer feedback, lab-grown Moissanite now closely mirrors its natural counterpart in nearly every respect. The only distinction lies in its age—natural Moissanite's ancient history remains unmatched by its lab-grown version.<\/p>","text_font_size":"body-medium","padding_bottom":16}}},"block_order":["heading-2-1","text-2-1"],"disabled":true,"settings":{"image_1":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Scientists_successfully_grow_moissanite_in_lab.jpg","image_width":"one-half","text_alignment":"text-left","layout":"","width":"wrapper--full","height":"image-height","mobile_height":"image-height--mobile","reverse_blocks":false,"color_scheme":"","padding_top":50,"padding_bottom":50,"show_placeholder":true}},"section_video_dkMJkE":{"type":"section-video","settings":{"video":"shopify:\/\/files\/videos\/Helzberg Diamonds _ Buy Diamonds, Jewelry Engagement Rings & Luxury Watches (1).mp4","show_video_popup":false,"video_popup_social":"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=_9VUPq3SxOc","title":"Laboratory-grown moissanite","heading_font_size":"heading-large","text":"","text_font_size":"body-medium","flex_align":"align--middle-center","link_text":"","link":"","button_type":"btn--primary","button_size":"","button_style":"btn--outline","show_arrow":false,"desktop_height":"screen-height-one-half","mobile_height":"image-height--mobile","width":"wrapper--full-padded","color_scheme":"","show_text_background":false,"color":"#ffffff","padding_top":0,"padding_bottom":0,"heading_tag":"automatic"}},"section_text_with_products_BH3htb":{"type":"section-text-with-products","settings":{"subheading":"","heading":"To meet rising demand, scientists have recreated Moissanite in labs, perfecting it through innovation and feedback. Today, lab-grown Moissanite is nearly identical to its natural form, with the only difference being its age and history.","width":"wrapper","text_font_size_px_desktop":24,"text_align_desktop":"text-left","text_font_size_px_mobile":21,"text_align_mobile":"text-left--mobile","color_scheme":"","padding_top":0,"padding_bottom":0}},"section_double_Nf7Fha":{"type":"section-double","blocks":{"heading_yefrhh":{"type":"heading","settings":{"title":"","heading_font_size":"heading-large","padding_bottom":16,"heading_tag":"automatic"}},"text_fqRwpd":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>On the Mohs scale, Moissanite ranks 9.25—harder than most gems, second only to diamond and boron nitride. With a higher refractive index than diamonds, it displays an even more brilliant rainbow fire. More than just a gemstone, Moissanite is a cosmic treasure worthy of admiration.<\/p>","text_font_size":"body-medium","padding_bottom":16}}},"block_order":["heading_yefrhh","text_fqRwpd"],"settings":{"image_1":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Moissanite_is_not_just_a_gemstone_it_is_a_gift_from_the_cosmos.png","image_width":"one-half","text_alignment":"text-left","layout":"is-reversed","width":"wrapper--full","height":"screen-height-three-quarters","mobile_height":"screen-height-one-half--mobile","reverse_blocks":false,"color_scheme":"","padding_top":0,"padding_bottom":50,"show_placeholder":true}},"section_double_67tCeX":{"type":"section-double","blocks":{"heading_eKE4g3":{"type":"heading","settings":{"title":"Is moissanite a fake diamond?","heading_font_size":"heading-large","padding_bottom":16,"heading_tag":"automatic"}},"text_HqEFQg":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>Two people may look like twins without being related—appearances alone can mislead us. Similarly, while De Beers’ famous slogan “A Diamond is Forever” made diamonds the symbol of love, not everyone can afford them. Diamonds are extraordinary, but true love is not defined by owning one; jewelry should simply enhance one’s presence.<\/p>","text_font_size":"body-medium","padding_bottom":16}}},"block_order":["heading_eKE4g3","text_HqEFQg"],"settings":{"image_1":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Is_moissanite_a_fake_diamond.jpg","image_width":"one-half","text_alignment":"text-left","layout":"","width":"wrapper--full","height":"image-height","mobile_height":"image-height--mobile","reverse_blocks":false,"color_scheme":"","padding_top":0,"padding_bottom":0,"show_placeholder":true}},"section_double_RDC3FA":{"type":"section-double","blocks":{"heading_Btyhar":{"type":"heading","settings":{"title":"Gift from the Universe","heading_font_size":"heading-large","padding_bottom":16,"heading_tag":"automatic"}},"text_p8qYmL":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>Moissanite is like a gift from the universe—an affordable alternative to diamonds without sacrificing beauty. True love values the meaning behind a gift, not its price. With Moissanite, you can enjoy the elegance of diamond-like designs without financial strain.<\/p>","text_font_size":"body-medium","padding_bottom":16}}},"block_order":["heading_Btyhar","text_p8qYmL"],"settings":{"image_1":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Gift_from_the_Universe.jpg","image_width":"one-half","text_alignment":"text-left","layout":"is-reversed","width":"wrapper--full","height":"image-height","mobile_height":"image-height--mobile","reverse_blocks":false,"color_scheme":"","padding_top":50,"padding_bottom":0,"show_placeholder":true}},"section_text_with_products_EFefFh":{"type":"section-text-with-products","settings":{"subheading":"","heading":"For those seeking diamonds, may Moissanite remind you that love and beauty are never defined by a single standard.","width":"wrapper","text_font_size_px_desktop":40,"text_align_desktop":"text-center","text_font_size_px_mobile":24,"text_align_mobile":"text-center--mobile","color_scheme":"","padding_top":7,"padding_bottom":10}},"divider":{"type":"section-divider","settings":{"show_line":true,"width":"wrapper--full-padded","color_scheme":"","padding_top":31,"padding_bottom":50}},"section_announcement_XfdJiU":{"type":"section-announcement","blocks":{"text_GjBpDX":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p><strong>SolariiJewelry<\/strong> |